2. I leave it all with Je-sus, For He knows How to steal the bit - ter

And my woe; When by faith I saw Him On the tree, Heard His small, still
From life's woes; How to gild the tear-drop With His smile, Make the desert
-
whisper, 'Tis for thee; From my heart the burden Rolled a-way-

English.
3 I leave it all with Jesus
Day by day;
Faith can firmly trust Him
Come what may;
Hope has dropped her anchor,
Found her rest,
In the calm, sure haven
Of His breast;
99
Rit.
N
Happy day! From my heart the burden Rolled a-way-Happy day!
All seems light. When my weakness leaneth On His might, All seems light.
9:
: Love esteems it heaven
To abide-At His side. :
4 Oh, leave it all with Jesus,
Drooping soul!
Tell not half thy story,
But the whole.
Worlds on worlds are hanging
On His hand,
Life and death are waiting
His command;
: Yet His tender bosom
Makes thee room-Oh, come home.:
